snippet.textDisplay: @Weary Host A virus is nothing more then a simple protein chain, it has no metabolic function, it has no respiratory system, it is not alive, it does not replicate.   The idea that a virus infects cells  and then makes copies of it self is completely made up to support the hypothesis of communicable diseases.   There is no such thing as naturally occurring communicable disease.    Where do viruses come from?  What is their purpose?   If you ask these question to modern accredited virologist, they will tell you they do not know.   Because they are paid to perpetuate a lie that viruses cause disease.    Naturally occurring viruses are created by your own immune system as a response to environmental changes.   It is the means by which cells detox.
